def: To cover again. Sir W. Scott.
Pertaining to, or obtained from, bile; as, choleic acid.
A sieve. [Written also tems, and tempse.] [Prov. Eng.]Halliwell. Temse bread, Temsed bread, Temse loaf, bread made of flourbetter sifted than common fluor. [Prov. Eng.]
The property or state of being biliteral.
The act of drawing the warp threads through the heddle-eyes ofa weaver's harness; the harness itself. Knight.
To fill, or become full, again.
